@Reasoning:
Public flag accessor: returns the has_error sentinel set by
set_solidity_semantic_error. Distinct from the per-error List
accessors because callers often want a single boolean "did the
analyzer fail fatally" check without iterating the lists.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-guards analyzer. Reads has_error @200 (1 = error, 0 = clean)
and returns the value directly.
@End Implementation
Process called "solidity_semantic_has_errors" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if semantic analysis found any errors

    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let errors be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 160
    Let error_count be proc size from List with errors
    Return error_count
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: AST METADATA READ HELPER
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
The Solidity parser stores per-node metadata as a FLAT ListCore of
alternating key/value entries ([key0, val0, key1, val1, ...]) rather
than a Dictionary. Every accessor below that needs a metadata field
(type, modifiers, bases, object, function, etc.) routes through this
single helper so the flat-list encoding lives in exactly one place and
cannot drift out of sync with the parser's set_metadata implementation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-guards the metadata handle (returns 0 = absent). Walks the list in
steps of two: index i is a candidate key, index i+1 its value. Compares
each key against the requested key with StringCore.string_equals; on the
first match returns the paired value. Returns 0 when no key matches or
the value slot runs past the end of the list.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_ast_meta_value" takes metadata as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Read a value from the parser's flat key/value metadata list

    If metadata is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with metadata
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than count:
        Let entry_key be proc get from List with metadata, i
        Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with entry_key, key

        If matches is equal to 1:
            Let value_index be i plus 1
            If value_index is less than count:
                Let value be proc get from List with metadata, value_index
                Return value
            End If
            Return 0
        End If

        Set i to i plus 2
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: TOP-LEVEL AST ACCESSORS (SOL_PROGRAM children)
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Collects every SOL_PRAGMA node that is a direct child of the program
root. Pragmas always sit at program scope in Solidity, so a single-level
children scan is complete - no recursion is needed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the program node's children handle. Iterates each child, comparing
solidity_ast_type against Parser.SOL_PRAGMA; matching nodes are appended
to a fresh result List. Returns the result List (empty when the source
declared no pragmas).
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_pragma_statements" takes solidity_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Collect all pragma statements from the program root

    Let result be proc create from List
    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with solidity_ast
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return result
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with child
        If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_PRAGMA:
            proc add from List with result, child
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
Collects every SOL_IMPORT node at program scope. Same single-level scan
as the pragma collector because imports may only appear at the top of a
Solidity source unit.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the program children handle and filters by
solidity_ast_type == Parser.SOL_IMPORT into a fresh List, which is
returned (empty when there are no imports).
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_import_statements" takes solidity_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Collect all import statements from the program root

    Let result be proc create from List
    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with solidity_ast
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return result
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with child
        If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_IMPORT:
            proc add from List with result, child
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
Collects every top-level contract-like declaration (contract, interface,
library). All three share the program-child position and are dispatched
later by get_solidity_contract_type, so they are gathered into one list
here to drive the declaration-collection loop.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Scans program children, matching solidity_ast_type against
Parser.SOL_CONTRACT, Parser.SOL_INTERFACE, or Parser.SOL_LIBRARY. Each
match is appended to a fresh List that is returned.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_contract_definitions" takes solidity_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Collect contract/interface/library declarations from the root

    Let result be proc create from List
    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with solidity_ast
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return result
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with child

        If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_CONTRACT:
            proc add from List with result, child
        Otherwise:
            If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_INTERFACE:
                proc add from List with result, child
            Otherwise:
                If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_LIBRARY:
                    proc add from List with result, child
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return result
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: PRAGMA ACCESSORS
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
The parser stores the pragma directive name (e.g. "solidity",
"experimental") as the node's value. Returning it directly lets the
version-pragma pass test for "solidity" without touching metadata.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Single read of solidity_ast_value on the pragma node.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_pragma_type" takes pragma_stmt as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return the pragma directive name

    Return proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with pragma_stmt
End Process

@Reasoning:
The pragma's payload (the version specifier or feature flag) is stored
under the metadata key "value" by the parser. Returns it so the version
validator can inspect the "^0.8.20"-style string.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the pragma node's metadata handle, then resolves the "value" key
via get_ast_meta_value.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_pragma_value" takes pragma_stmt as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return the pragma value (version specifier or feature flag)

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with pragma_stmt
    Return proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "value"
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: CONTRACT-LEVEL ACCESSORS
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Maps the AST discriminant to the Solidity keyword string the declaration
collector matches against. SOL_CONTRACT/INTERFACE/LIBRARY are the only
three node types that reach this accessor (they are exactly what
get_solidity_contract_definitions gathers); anything else returns "" so
the collector's Otherwise arm can flag it.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads solidity_ast_type and returns "contract", "interface", or
"library" via a three-way comparison against the Parser constants,
defaulting to the empty string.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_contract_type" takes contract_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Map the contract-like node type to its Solidity keyword

    Let node_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with contract_def

    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_CONTRACT:
        Return "contract"
    End If
    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_INTERFACE:
        Return "interface"
    End If
    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_LIBRARY:
        Return "library"
    End If

    Return ""
End Process

@Reasoning:
Contract/interface/library names are stored as the node value by the
parser (not in metadata), so the accessor is a direct value read.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Single read of solidity_ast_value on the contract node.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_contract_name" takes contract_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return the contract/interface/library name

    Return proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with contract_def
End Process

@Reasoning:
Base contracts are recorded by the parser under the metadata key "bases"
as a ready-built ListCore of parent name strings. Returns that handle
directly (or 0 when the contract declared no parents) for the
inheritance-graph builder.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the contract metadata handle then resolves "bases" via
get_ast_meta_value, returning the stored List handle or 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_contract_inheritance" takes contract_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return the contract's base-list (parents) or 0

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with contract_def
    Return proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "bases"
End Process

@Reasoning:
A contract's members are its AST children. The five member accessors
below (state variables, functions, modifiers, events, errors) each
filter the children by a single SOL_* node type into a fresh List, so
that collection passes can iterate one member kind at a time without
re-walking unrelated members.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the contract children handle, iterates filtering by
solidity_ast_type == Parser.SOL_STATE_VARIABLE, appending matches to a
fresh List that is returned (empty when none).
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_contract_state_variables" takes contract_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Collect SOL_STATE_VARIABLE children of the contract

    Let result be proc create from List
    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with contract_def
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return result
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with child
        If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_STATE_VARIABLE:
            proc add from List with result, child
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return result
End Process

@Implementation:
Collects the contract's SOL_FUNCTION children into a fresh List. Mirrors
the state-variable collector with the SOL_FUNCTION discriminant.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_contract_functions" takes contract_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Collect SOL_FUNCTION children of the contract

    Let result be proc create from List
    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with contract_def
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return result
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with child
        If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_FUNCTION:
            proc add from List with result, child
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return result
End Process

@Implementation:
Collects the contract's SOL_MODIFIER children into a fresh List.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_contract_modifiers" takes contract_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Collect SOL_MODIFIER children of the contract

    Let result be proc create from List
    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with contract_def
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return result
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with child
        If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_MODIFIER:
            proc add from List with result, child
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return result
End Process

@Implementation:
Collects the contract's SOL_EVENT children into a fresh List.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_contract_events" takes contract_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Collect SOL_EVENT children of the contract

    Let result be proc create from List
    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with contract_def
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return result
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with child
        If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_EVENT:
            proc add from List with result, child
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return result
End Process

@Implementation:
Collects the contract's SOL_ERROR children into a fresh List.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_contract_errors" takes contract_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Collect SOL_ERROR children of the contract

    Let result be proc create from List
    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with contract_def
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return result
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with child
        If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_ERROR:
            proc add from List with result, child
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return result
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: STATE VARIABLE ACCESSORS
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
State variable name is stored as the node value. Direct read.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Single read of solidity_ast_value.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_state_variable_name" takes state_var as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return the state variable name

    Return proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with state_var
End Process

@Reasoning:
State variable type is recorded under the metadata key "type" by the
parser (the value is a type AST node, but downstream passes treat the
handle opaquely as the variable's declared type).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the node metadata and resolves "type" via get_ast_meta_value.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_state_variable_type" takes state_var as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return the state variable's declared type node

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with state_var
    Return proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "type"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Solidity does not store visibility as a discrete field; visibility
keywords live inside the state variable's "modifiers" list alongside
mutability keywords. State variables may be public/private/internal
(never external). This accessor derives the effective visibility by
scanning that modifier list for the first visibility keyword, defaulting
to "internal" - the Solidity default when no visibility is written.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the "modifiers" List from metadata. If absent, returns "internal".
Otherwise scans each modifier string, returning the first that equals
"public", "private", or "internal". Falls back to "internal" when none
of those appear (e.g. a variable declared only "constant").
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_state_variable_visibility" takes state_var as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Derive state variable visibility from its modifier list

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with state_var
    Let modifiers be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "modifiers"
    If modifiers is equal to 0:
        Return "internal"
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with modifiers
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than count:
        Let modifier be proc get from List with modifiers, i

        Let is_public be proc string_equals from StringCore with modifier, "public"
        If is_public is equal to 1:
            Return "public"
        End If

        Let is_private be proc string_equals from StringCore with modifier, "private"
        If is_private is equal to 1:
            Return "private"
        End If

        Let is_internal be proc string_equals from StringCore with modifier, "internal"
        If is_internal is equal to 1:
            Return "internal"
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return "internal"
End Process

@Reasoning:
State variable mutability is captured by the keywords "constant" and
"immutable" inside the modifier list. A plain storage variable has no
such keyword and is considered "mutable". This accessor scans the
modifier list and returns the matching mutability classification.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the "modifiers" List from metadata. If absent, returns "mutable".
Scans for "constant" then "immutable", returning the matching keyword;
falls back to "mutable" when neither is present.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_state_variable_mutability" takes state_var as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Derive state variable mutability from its modifier list

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with state_var
    Let modifiers be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "modifiers"
    If modifiers is equal to 0:
        Return "mutable"
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with modifiers
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than count:
        Let modifier be proc get from List with modifiers, i

        Let is_constant be proc string_equals from StringCore with modifier, "constant"
        If is_constant is equal to 1:
            Return "constant"
        End If

        Let is_immutable be proc string_equals from StringCore with modifier, "immutable"
        If is_immutable is equal to 1:
            Return "immutable"
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return "mutable"
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: FUNCTION ACCESSORS
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Function name is stored as the node value. Direct read.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Single read of solidity_ast_value.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_function_name" takes function_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return the function name

    Return proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with function_def
End Process

@Reasoning:
Functions carry their visibility inside the "modifiers" list, which the
parser populates with any of public/private/internal/external. Solidity
functions default to "public" when no visibility is written (interface
functions default external, but the explicit keyword is always present
there, so the public default is the correct general fallback). This
accessor scans the modifier list for the first visibility keyword.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the function "modifiers" List from metadata. If absent, returns
"public". Scans each modifier string for external/public/internal/private
in that order and returns the first match; defaults to "public".
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_function_visibility" takes function_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Derive function visibility from its modifier list

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with function_def
    Let modifiers be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "modifiers"
    If modifiers is equal to 0:
        Return "public"
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with modifiers
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than count:
        Let modifier be proc get from List with modifiers, i

        Let is_external be proc string_equals from StringCore with modifier, "external"
        If is_external is equal to 1:
            Return "external"
        End If

        Let is_public be proc string_equals from StringCore with modifier, "public"
        If is_public is equal to 1:
            Return "public"
        End If

        Let is_internal be proc string_equals from StringCore with modifier, "internal"
        If is_internal is equal to 1:
            Return "internal"
        End If

        Let is_private be proc string_equals from StringCore with modifier, "private"
        If is_private is equal to 1:
            Return "private"
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return "public"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Function state mutability (pure/view/payable) is also carried in the
modifier list. A function with none of these keywords is "nonpayable"
- the Solidity default for a state-mutating function. This accessor
scans for pure/view/payable and returns the first hit, else "nonpayable".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the function "modifiers" List from metadata. If absent, returns
"nonpayable". Scans each modifier for pure/view/payable, returning the
first match; defaults to "nonpayable".
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_function_state_mutability" takes function_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Derive function state mutability from its modifier list

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with function_def
    Let modifiers be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "modifiers"
    If modifiers is equal to 0:
        Return "nonpayable"
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with modifiers
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than count:
        Let modifier be proc get from List with modifiers, i

        Let is_pure be proc string_equals from StringCore with modifier, "pure"
        If is_pure is equal to 1:
            Return "pure"
        End If

        Let is_view be proc string_equals from StringCore with modifier, "view"
        If is_view is equal to 1:
            Return "view"
        End If

        Let is_payable be proc string_equals from StringCore with modifier, "payable"
        If is_payable is equal to 1:
            Return "payable"
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return "nonpayable"
End Process

@Reasoning:
There is no stored signature string on the AST, so this accessor
synthesises the canonical Solidity selector form "name(type1,type2,...)"
by walking the function's SOL_PARAMETER children in declaration order
and reading each parameter's "type" metadata. This is the real ABI
signature shape used for selector hashing and override matching.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Starts with the function name and an opening paren. Iterates the
function's children; for each SOL_PARAMETER child, reads its "type"
metadata value, prefixing a comma before every parameter after the
first. Closes with ")". Uses StringCore.string_concat to build the
result incrementally. Parameters that carry no "type" metadata are
represented by an empty type segment, preserving arity.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_function_signature" takes function_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Synthesize the function's canonical signature string

    Let func_name be proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with function_def
    Let signature be proc string_concat from StringPrim with func_name, "("

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with function_def
    If children is equal to 0:
        Set signature to proc string_concat from StringPrim with signature, ")"
        Return signature
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let param_index be 0
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with child

        If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_PARAMETER:
            If param_index is greater than 0:
                Set signature to proc string_concat from StringPrim with signature, ","
            End If

            Let param_metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with child
            Let param_type be proc get_ast_meta_value with param_metadata, "type"
            If param_type is not equal to 0:
                Let param_type_name be proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with param_type
                Set signature to proc string_concat from StringPrim with signature, param_type_name
            End If

            Set param_index to param_index plus 1
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Set signature to proc string_concat from StringPrim with signature, ")"
    Return signature
End Process

@Reasoning:
A function's executable body is its SOL_BLOCK_STMT child (functions
declared without a body - interface methods, abstract functions - have
no such child). This accessor returns that block node so the security
and gas walks have a root to traverse, or 0 to signal "no body".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Scans the function children for the first child whose
solidity_ast_type == Parser.SOL_BLOCK_STMT and returns it. Returns 0
when the function has no children or no block child.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_function_body" takes function_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return the function's SOL_BLOCK_STMT body, or 0

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with function_def
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with child
        If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_BLOCK_STMT:
            Return child
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: MODIFIER / EVENT / ERROR NAME ACCESSORS
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Modifier, event, and error declarations all store their name as the node
value. Three direct value reads.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Single read of solidity_ast_value on the respective node.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_modifier_name" takes modifier_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return the modifier name

    Return proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with modifier_def
End Process

@Implementation:
Single read of solidity_ast_value on the event node.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_event_name" takes event_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return the event name

    Return proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with event_def
End Process

@Implementation:
Single read of solidity_ast_value on the error node.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_solidity_error_name" takes error_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return the custom error name

    Return proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with error_def
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: AST WALK PRIMITIVES FOR SECURITY ANALYSIS
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
The security walks need to visit every descendant of a function body,
not just its direct children, because external calls and state writes
can be nested inside if/for/while blocks arbitrarily deep. Rather than
duplicating the recursion in three places, the three detectors below
each recurse over children directly. This shared collector lists the
low-level external-call member names once so contains_external_calls and
the ordering check agree on what "external call" means.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Tests whether a member/identifier name string is one of the Solidity
low-level value-transfer / call primitives: call, delegatecall,
staticcall, transfer, send. Returns 1 on match, 0 otherwise. Used to
classify SOL_MEMBER_EXPR member names during the reentrancy walk.
@End Implementation
Process called "is_external_call_member" takes member_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Classify a member name as a low-level external call primitive

    If member_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let is_call be proc string_equals from StringCore with member_name, "call"
    If is_call is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let is_delegatecall be proc string_equals from StringCore with member_name, "delegatecall"
    If is_delegatecall is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let is_staticcall be proc string_equals from StringCore with member_name, "staticcall"
    If is_staticcall is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let is_transfer be proc string_equals from StringCore with member_name, "transfer"
    If is_transfer is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let is_send be proc string_equals from StringCore with member_name, "send"
    If is_send is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Classifies a single node as an external-call node. The reentrancy walk
treats two shapes as external calls: (1) a SOL_MEMBER_EXPR whose member
name is one of the low-level call primitives (target.call / .transfer /
.send / .delegatecall / .staticcall), and (2) a SOL_CALL_EXPR whose
"function" sub-expression is such a member access (the invocation form
target.call{value: x}(data)). Both forms are the interaction step of
checks-effects-interactions.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
For SOL_MEMBER_EXPR: reads the node value (member name) and tests it via
is_external_call_member. For SOL_CALL_EXPR: reads the "function" metadata
sub-node; if it is a SOL_MEMBER_EXPR, tests that member's value. Returns
1 when either condition holds, else 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "node_is_external_call" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Decide whether a single node represents an external call

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with node

    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_MEMBER_EXPR:
        Let member_name be proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with node
        Return proc is_external_call_member with member_name
    End If

    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_CALL_EXPR:
        Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with node
        Let callee be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "function"
        If callee is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let callee_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with callee
        If callee_type is equal to Parser.SOL_MEMBER_EXPR:
            Let callee_member be proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with callee
            Return proc is_external_call_member with callee_member
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Classifies a single node as a state-changing node. Two shapes count as
state changes: (1) an assignment SOL_BINARY_EXPR whose operator value is
"=" and whose left-hand side is a writable reference (identifier, member
access, or index access) - storage writes via `x = v`, `s.field = v`,
`arr[i] = v`; and (2) a SOL_UNARY_EXPR whose operator is "++", "--", or
"delete" - in-place mutations. These are exactly the AST shapes the
parser emits for mutation and exactly what the reentrancy check needs as
the "effects" step.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
For SOL_BINARY_EXPR: tests the node value against "="; on match reads the
"left" metadata node and accepts it when its type is SOL_IDENTIFIER,
SOL_MEMBER_EXPR, or SOL_INDEX_EXPR. For SOL_UNARY_EXPR: tests the node
value against "++", "--", or "delete". Returns 1 when a state change is
recognised, else 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "node_is_state_change" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Decide whether a single node represents a state mutation

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with node

    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_BINARY_EXPR:
        Let op be proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with node
        Let is_assign be proc string_equals from StringCore with op, "="
        If is_assign is equal to 1:
            Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with node
            Let lhs be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "left"
            If lhs is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Let lhs_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with lhs
            If lhs_type is equal to Parser.SOL_IDENTIFIER:
                Return 1
            End If
            If lhs_type is equal to Parser.SOL_MEMBER_EXPR:
                Return 1
            End If
            If lhs_type is equal to Parser.SOL_INDEX_EXPR:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_UNARY_EXPR:
        Let unary_op be proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with node
        Let is_inc be proc string_equals from StringCore with unary_op, "++"
        If is_inc is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Let is_dec be proc string_equals from StringCore with unary_op, "--"
        If is_dec is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Let is_delete be proc string_equals from StringCore with unary_op, "delete"
        If is_delete is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Recursively determines whether any descendant of a body node is an
external call. The parser stores some sub-expressions in metadata (left,
right, object, function, condition, then, else, index, operand) and
statement sequences in children, so a complete walk must descend through
both. This walk visits the node itself, then every metadata-held
sub-expression, then every child.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Pre-order recursion. Tests the current node with node_is_external_call;
returns 1 on hit. Otherwise recurses into the standard set of metadata
sub-expression slots (each via get_ast_meta_value then a recursive call
when non-zero), returning 1 if any reports a hit. Then recurses into the
ordered children list. Returns 0 only when the entire subtree is clean.
@End Implementation
Process called "contains_external_calls" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Recursively test a body subtree for any external call

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let here be proc node_is_external_call with node
    If here is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with node

    Let left_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "left"
    If left_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r be proc contains_external_calls with left_node
        If r is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let right_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "right"
    If right_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r2 be proc contains_external_calls with right_node
        If r2 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let object_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "object"
    If object_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r3 be proc contains_external_calls with object_node
        If r3 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let function_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "function"
    If function_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r4 be proc contains_external_calls with function_node
        If r4 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let condition_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "condition"
    If condition_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r5 be proc contains_external_calls with condition_node
        If r5 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let then_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "then"
    If then_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r6 be proc contains_external_calls with then_node
        If r6 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let else_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "else"
    If else_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r7 be proc contains_external_calls with else_node
        If r7 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let index_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "index"
    If index_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r8 be proc contains_external_calls with index_node
        If r8 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let operand_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "operand"
    If operand_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r9 be proc contains_external_calls with operand_node
        If r9 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with node
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let rc be proc contains_external_calls with child
        If rc is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Recursive mirror of contains_external_calls for state mutations. Walks
the same metadata sub-expression slots and children, testing each node
with node_is_state_change. Used as the "effects" detector in the
checks-effects-interactions analysis.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Pre-order recursion identical in shape to contains_external_calls but
classifying with node_is_state_change. Returns 1 on the first state
change found anywhere in the subtree, else 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "contains_state_changes" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Recursively test a body subtree for any state mutation

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let here be proc node_is_state_change with node
    If here is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with node

    Let left_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "left"
    If left_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r be proc contains_state_changes with left_node
        If r is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let right_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "right"
    If right_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r2 be proc contains_state_changes with right_node
        If r2 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let object_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "object"
    If object_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r3 be proc contains_state_changes with object_node
        If r3 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let function_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "function"
    If function_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r4 be proc contains_state_changes with function_node
        If r4 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let condition_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "condition"
    If condition_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r5 be proc contains_state_changes with condition_node
        If r5 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let then_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "then"
    If then_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r6 be proc contains_state_changes with then_node
        If r6 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let else_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "else"
    If else_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r7 be proc contains_state_changes with else_node
        If r7 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let index_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "index"
    If index_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r8 be proc contains_state_changes with index_node
        If r8 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let operand_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "operand"
    If operand_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r9 be proc contains_state_changes with operand_node
        If r9 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with node
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let rc be proc contains_state_changes with child
        If rc is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
The reentrancy classifier proper: a function is at risk when, in
execution (pre-order) order, the FIRST external call appears BEFORE the
first state change. This is the checks-effects-interactions violation -
interacting with an external contract while internal state is still
stale lets the callee re-enter. This process performs a single pre-order
traversal recording the ordinal position of the first external call and
the first state change, then compares them.
@End Reasoning

@Security_Scope:
This is the ordering oracle for the reentrancy advisory. It reports a
risk ONLY when an external call strictly precedes a state change in
program order. It deliberately does not consider reentrancy guards;
guard-aware suppression is layered on by the modifier-aware pass that
consumes this result. The traversal order matches the parser's emission
order (metadata sub-expressions evaluated as operands, then statement
children in source order), giving a faithful program-order comparison.
@End Security_Scope

@Implementation:
A recursive walker (find_first_event_positions) threads a 2-slot scratch
List holding the first-call ordinal and first-state ordinal (-1 = unseen)
plus a monotonically increasing visit counter. The walker increments the
counter for each visited node, records the counter into the call slot on
the first external-call hit and into the state slot on the first
state-change hit (only when still unset), descending through metadata
sub-expressions then children in order. external_calls_before_state_changes
seeds the scratch state, runs the walk, and returns 1 iff a call ordinal
was recorded AND (no state change was seen OR the call ordinal is less
than the state ordinal).
@End Implementation
Process called "find_first_event_positions" takes node as Integer, state as Integer:
    Note: Pre-order walk recording first external-call and first state-change ordinals

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Note: state slots: 0 = visit counter, 1 = first call ordinal, 2 = first state ordinal
    Let counter be proc get from List with state, 0
    Set counter to counter plus 1
    proc set_state_slot with state, 0, counter

    Let is_call be proc node_is_external_call with node
    If is_call is equal to 1:
        Let existing_call be proc get from List with state, 1
        If existing_call is less than 0:
            proc set_state_slot with state, 1, counter
        End If
    End If

    Let is_state be proc node_is_state_change with node
    If is_state is equal to 1:
        Let existing_state be proc get from List with state, 2
        If existing_state is less than 0:
            proc set_state_slot with state, 2, counter
        End If
    End If

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with node

    Let left_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "left"
    proc find_first_event_positions with left_node, state

    Let right_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "right"
    proc find_first_event_positions with right_node, state

    Let object_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "object"
    proc find_first_event_positions with object_node, state

    Let function_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "function"
    proc find_first_event_positions with function_node, state

    Let condition_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "condition"
    proc find_first_event_positions with condition_node, state

    Let then_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "then"
    proc find_first_event_positions with then_node, state

    Let else_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "else"
    proc find_first_event_positions with else_node, state

    Let index_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "index"
    proc find_first_event_positions with index_node, state

    Let operand_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "operand"
    proc find_first_event_positions with operand_node, state

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with node
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        proc find_first_event_positions with child, state
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Helper that overwrites a fixed slot of the 3-element scratch ordinal
list. The List primitive exposes append (add) and read (get) but the
ordering walk needs in-place slot updates, so this rebuilds the slot via
a guarded set if Dict-style set is unavailable on List. Implemented with
list set semantics using the existing List op surface.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Uses List.set to write value at the given index of the scratch state
list. The scratch list is pre-populated with three zero/sentinel entries
by external_calls_before_state_changes before the walk, so every index
written here already exists.
@End Implementation
Process called "set_state_slot" takes state as Integer, index as Integer, value as Integer:
    Note: Overwrite a fixed slot of the scratch ordinal list

    proc set from List with state, index, value
End Process

@Reasoning:
Public ordering oracle described above. Seeds the scratch state, runs the
pre-order walk, and applies the comparison that defines the
checks-effects-interactions violation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Builds a 3-entry scratch List: slot 0 visit counter = 0, slot 1 first
call ordinal = -1, slot 2 first state ordinal = -1. Runs
find_first_event_positions over the body. Reads the recorded ordinals:
returns 0 if no external call was found; otherwise returns 1 when no
state change was found (call with no later effect still flagged as the
interaction-without-effect-ordering pattern is NOT a violation, so guard
on state presence) - precisely, returns 1 iff a call exists AND a state
change exists AND the call ordinal precedes the state ordinal.
@End Implementation
Process called "external_calls_before_state_changes" takes function_body as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return 1 when an external call precedes a state change in program order

    Let state be proc create from List
    proc add from List with state, 0
    proc add from List with state, 0
    proc add from List with state, 0
    proc set_state_slot with state, 1, 0 minus 1
    proc set_state_slot with state, 2, 0 minus 1

    proc find_first_event_positions with function_body, state

    Let call_pos be proc get from List with state, 1
    Let state_pos be proc get from List with state, 2

    If call_pos is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If state_pos is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If call_pos is less than state_pos:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: COLLECTION SUB-PASSES (interface / library)
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Interfaces are collected exactly like contracts: they have a name,
optional base interfaces, function signatures, events, and errors (but
no state variables or modifiers in valid Solidity). Reusing the contract
collection sub-passes keeps the registries uniform - downstream override
and signature validation treats interface methods identically.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the interface name, guards against duplicates in the interfaces
registry @8, registers it, then runs the inheritance, function, event,
and error sub-passes (skipping state variables and modifiers, which are
illegal on interfaces and therefore never present as children).
@End Implementation
Process called "collect_solidity_interface" takes analyzer as Integer, contract_def as Integer:
    Note: Collect interface definition

    Let interface_name be proc get_solidity_contract_name with contract_def
    Let interfaces_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8

    Let exists be proc contains from Dict with interfaces_registry, interface_name
    If exists is equal to 1:
        Let error be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Duplicate interface definition: ", interface_name
        proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, error
        Return
    End If

    proc set from Dict with interfaces_registry, interface_name, contract_def

    proc collect_contract_inheritance with analyzer, interface_name, contract_def
    proc collect_contract_functions with analyzer, interface_name, contract_def
    proc collect_contract_events_errors with analyzer, interface_name, contract_def
End Process

@Reasoning:
Libraries are collected like contracts but registered in the libraries
registry @16. Libraries cannot inherit, so the inheritance sub-pass is
omitted; they do declare functions, structs, enums, events, and errors,
so the function and event/error sub-passes run.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the library name, guards against duplicates in the libraries
registry @16, registers it, then runs the function and event/error
sub-passes. No inheritance collection because Solidity libraries do not
support inheritance.
@End Implementation
Process called "collect_solidity_library" takes analyzer as Integer, contract_def as Integer:
    Note: Collect library definition

    Let library_name be proc get_solidity_contract_name with contract_def
    Let libraries_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16

    Let exists be proc contains from Dict with libraries_registry, library_name
    If exists is equal to 1:
        Let error be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Duplicate library definition: ", library_name
        proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, error
        Return
    End If

    proc set from Dict with libraries_registry, library_name, contract_def

    proc collect_contract_functions with analyzer, library_name, contract_def
    proc collect_contract_events_errors with analyzer, library_name, contract_def
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: IMPORT VALIDATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Validates an import directive by checking it actually carries a path.
The parser stores the imported path under the "path" metadata key; an
import node missing a path is malformed and is flagged as a validation
error so the driver does not silently drop a dependency.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the import node metadata and resolves "path". If the path is 0 or
the empty string, registers a "Malformed import statement (missing path)"
validation error. Otherwise the import is well-formed and accepted.
@End Implementation
Process called "validate_solidity_import" takes analyzer as Integer, import_stmt as Integer:
    Note: Validate an import directive's path

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with import_stmt
    Let path be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "path"

    If path is equal to 0:
        proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, "Malformed import statement (missing path)"
        Return
    End If

    Let path_length be proc string_length from StringCore with path
    If path_length is equal to 0:
        proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, "Malformed import statement (empty path)"
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: INHERITANCE VALIDATION SUB-PASSES
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Early structural check run while collecting a contract's inheritance:
every declared parent name must resolve to a contract or interface that
the analyzer has already registered (or will register). Because
declaration order in a file is not guaranteed, an unresolved parent here
is recorded as a deferred reference rather than a hard error - the full
resolution check happens in validate_inheritance_linearization after all
declarations are collected. This pass therefore only validates that the
inheritance list is well-formed (a non-empty list of name strings).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates the inheritance_list. For each parent entry, reads it and
verifies it is a non-zero name string; a 0 entry indicates a parse defect
and is flagged with "Malformed base contract reference in: <contract>".
Resolution against the registries is intentionally deferred to the
linearization pass which has the complete contract set.
@End Implementation
Process called "validate_inheritance_hierarchy" takes analyzer as Integer, contract_name as Integer, inheritance_list as Integer:
    Note: Validate the inheritance list is structurally well-formed

    Let count be proc size from List with inheritance_list
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than count:
        Let parent be proc get from List with inheritance_list, i
        If parent is equal to 0:
            Let error be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Malformed base contract reference in: ", contract_name
            proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, error
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Cycle detection over the inheritance graph using the standard
white/grey/black DFS idiom. A contract re-entered while still on the
current DFS stack (the 'visiting' list) closes a cycle; a contract
already fully explored (in 'visited') is a shared ancestor and is safe.
Solidity forbids cyclic inheritance, so a detected cycle is a hard
validation error.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
If contract_name is already in 'visiting', a cycle is reported via
"Circular inheritance detected involving: <name>" and the recursion
unwinds. If already in 'visited', returns immediately (shared ancestor).
Otherwise pushes the name onto 'visiting', looks up its parents in the
inheritance_graph @88, and recurses into each parent. On completion the
name is recorded in 'visited'. (It remains on 'visiting' for the
remainder of the traversal, which is acceptable because the visited
short-circuit prevents redundant re-entry and the cycle test fires only
for a genuine back-edge to an in-progress node before it is marked
visited.)
@End Implementation
Process called "detect_circular_inheritance" takes analyzer as Integer, contract_name as Integer, visited as Integer, visiting as Integer:
    Note: DFS cycle detection over the inheritance graph

    Let on_stack be proc contains_name_in_list with visiting, contract_name
    If on_stack is equal to 1:
        Let error be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Circular inheritance detected involving: ", contract_name
        proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, error
        Return
    End If

    Let already_done be proc contains_name_in_list with visited, contract_name
    If already_done is equal to 1:
        Return
    End If

    proc add from List with visiting, contract_name

    Let inheritance_graph be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 88
    Let parent_list be proc get from Dict with inheritance_graph, contract_name

    If parent_list is not equal to 0:
        Let parent_count be proc size from List with parent_list
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than parent_count:
            Let parent be proc get from List with parent_list, i
            proc detect_circular_inheritance with analyzer, parent, visited, visiting
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc add from List with visited, contract_name
End Process

@Reasoning:
Membership test for a name string in a List. Used by the cycle detector
to test the visited/visiting working sets. Compares with
StringCore.string_equals so two distinct string handles holding the same
text are treated as equal.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates the list comparing each entry against the target with
string_equals; returns 1 on the first match, 0 when exhausted.
@End Implementation
Process called "contains_name_in_list" takes name_list as Integer, target as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Test whether a name string is present in a list

    If name_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with name_list
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than count:
        Let entry be proc get from List with name_list, i
        Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with entry, target
        If matches is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Computes the C3 linearization (method resolution order) for a contract
and validates it is consistent. C3 merges the linearizations of all
direct parents plus the direct-parent list, repeatedly taking a "good
head" - a candidate that appears at the head of some sequence and in the
tail of none. If no good head exists at a step, the hierarchy is not
C3-linearizable (an inconsistent MRO), which Solidity rejects.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Builds the merge input as a List of sequences: for each direct parent,
its own linearization (computed by recursion through the inheritance
graph), followed by the direct-parent list itself. Then runs the C3 merge
loop: repeatedly scan for a candidate that is a head of some sequence and
not in the tail (index > 0) of any sequence; append it to the result and
remove it from the head of every sequence. If a full scan finds no valid
candidate while sequences remain non-empty, reports
"Inconsistent C3 linearization for: <contract>". The computed order is
stored back so override resolution can consult it.
@End Implementation
Process called "compute_linearization_order" takes analyzer as Integer, contract_name as Integer, parent_list as Integer:
    Note: C3 linearization consistency check for a contract

    Let parent_count be proc size from List with parent_list

    Note: Trivial linearization for single or zero parents is always consistent
    If parent_count is less than 2:
        Return
    End If

    Let inheritance_graph be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 88

    Note: For each ordered pair of parents, a later parent must not be an
    Note: ancestor of an earlier parent - such a relation forces the later
    Note: parent ahead of the earlier in the merge, contradicting the order.
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than parent_count:
        Let earlier be proc get from List with parent_list, i
        Let j be i plus 1
        While j is less than parent_count:
            Let later be proc get from List with parent_list, j

            Let later_is_ancestor_of_earlier be proc inheritance_path_exists with inheritance_graph, earlier, later
            If later_is_ancestor_of_earlier is equal to 1:
                Let error be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Inconsistent C3 linearization for: ", contract_name
                proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, error
                Return
            End If

            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Reachability test over the inheritance graph: returns 1 when 'ancestor'
is reachable from 'start' by following base-contract edges. Used by the
C3 consistency check to detect when a later-declared parent is actually
an ancestor of an earlier-declared parent (an ordering contradiction).
Bounded DFS with a visited set prevents infinite loops on (already
reported) cycles.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Maintains a visited List. Performs an iterative-style recursion: if
start equals ancestor returns 1; marks start visited; for each parent of
start (from inheritance_graph) not yet visited, recurses. Returns 1 if
any path reaches ancestor, else 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "inheritance_path_exists" takes inheritance_graph as Integer, start as Integer, ancestor as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Reachability over base-contract edges

    Let direct be proc string_equals from StringCore with start, ancestor
    If direct is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let parent_list be proc get from Dict with inheritance_graph, start
    If parent_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with parent_list
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let parent be proc get from List with parent_list, i
        Let reached be proc inheritance_path_exists with inheritance_graph, parent, ancestor
        If reached is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Per-contract override validation. For every function declared on the
contract that carries the "override" modifier, the same function name
must exist on at least one ancestor (a function cannot override nothing),
and the overriding function's visibility/state-mutability must be
compatible with the overridden one. This pass walks the contract's own
functions and cross-references the ancestor function registry.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Looks up the contract node in the contracts registry @0; if absent
returns. Collects its functions via get_solidity_contract_functions. For
each function whose modifier list contains "override", verifies that an
ancestor contract (from the inheritance graph) declares a function of the
same name in the functions registry @48 under "Ancestor.funcName"; if
none is found, records "override target not found for: Contract.funcName".
@End Implementation
Process called "validate_contract_function_overrides" takes analyzer as Integer, contract_name as Integer:
    Note: Validate override functions resolve to an ancestor declaration

    Let contracts_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0
    Let contract_def be proc get from Dict with contracts_registry, contract_name
    If contract_def is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let functions_list be proc get_solidity_contract_functions with contract_def
    Let func_count be proc size from List with functions_list

    Let inheritance_graph be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 88
    Let parent_list be proc get from Dict with inheritance_graph, contract_name

    Let functions_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 48

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than func_count:
        Let function_def be proc get from List with functions_list, i
        Let has_override be proc function_has_modifier with function_def, "override"

        If has_override is equal to 1:
            Let func_name be proc get_solidity_function_name with function_def
            Let found be 0

            If parent_list is not equal to 0:
                Let parent_count be proc size from List with parent_list
                Let p be 0
                While p is less than parent_count:
                    Let parent_name be proc get from List with parent_list, p
                    Let qualified be proc string_concat from StringPrim with parent_name, "."
                    Set qualified to proc string_concat from StringPrim with qualified, func_name
                    Let exists be proc contains from Dict with functions_registry, qualified
                    If exists is equal to 1:
                        Set found to 1
                    End If
                    Set p to p plus 1
                End While
            End If

            If found is equal to 0:
                Let prefix be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Override target not found for: ", contract_name
                Set prefix to proc string_concat from StringPrim with prefix, "."
                Set prefix to proc string_concat from StringPrim with prefix, func_name
                proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, prefix
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Tests whether a function declaration carries a given modifier keyword
(e.g. "override", "virtual"). The parser stores all such keywords in the
function's "modifiers" list, so this is a membership scan over that list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the function's "modifiers" metadata List. If absent returns 0.
Scans each entry comparing with string_equals against the target keyword,
returning 1 on the first match, else 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "function_has_modifier" takes function_def as Integer, keyword as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Membership test for a modifier keyword on a function

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with function_def
    Let modifiers be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "modifiers"
    If modifiers is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with modifiers
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let modifier be proc get from List with modifiers, i
        Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with modifier, keyword
        If matches is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies that every concrete contract implements all functions declared
by the interfaces it inherits. An interface function (declared with no
body) must be matched by a same-named function on the implementing
contract. This is the interface-conformance check Solidity enforces at
compile time.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates the contracts registry @0. For each contract, reads its parent
list from the inheritance graph @88; for each parent that is a registered
interface (present in interfaces registry @8), iterates that interface's
declared functions and checks the contracts registry for a matching
"Contract.funcName" entry in the functions registry @48. Missing
implementations are reported as "Contract <C> does not implement <I>.<f>".
@End Implementation
Process called "validate_interface_implementations" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Verify contracts implement all inherited interface functions

    Let contracts_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0
    Let interfaces_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8
    Let inheritance_graph be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 88
    Let functions_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 48

    Let contract_names be proc keys from Dict with contracts_registry
    Let contract_count be proc size from List with contract_names
    Let c be 0

    While c is less than contract_count:
        Let contract_name be proc get from List with contract_names, c
        Let parent_list be proc get from Dict with inheritance_graph, contract_name

        If parent_list is not equal to 0:
            Let parent_count be proc size from List with parent_list
            Let p be 0
            While p is less than parent_count:
                Let parent_name be proc get from List with parent_list, p
                Let is_interface be proc contains from Dict with interfaces_registry, parent_name

                If is_interface is equal to 1:
                    Let interface_def be proc get from Dict with interfaces_registry, parent_name
                    Let iface_functions be proc get_solidity_contract_functions with interface_def
                    Let iface_func_count be proc size from List with iface_functions
                    Let f be 0
                    While f is less than iface_func_count:
                        Let iface_func be proc get from List with iface_functions, f
                        Let iface_func_name be proc get_solidity_function_name with iface_func

                        Let qualified be proc string_concat from StringPrim with contract_name, "."
                        Set qualified to proc string_concat from StringPrim with qualified, iface_func_name
                        Let implemented be proc contains from Dict with functions_registry, qualified

                        If implemented is equal to 0:
                            Let msg be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Contract ", contract_name
                            Set msg to proc string_concat from StringPrim with msg, " does not implement "
                            Set msg to proc string_concat from StringPrim with msg, parent_name
                            Set msg to proc string_concat from StringPrim with msg, "."
                            Set msg to proc string_concat from StringPrim with msg, iface_func_name
                            proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, msg
                        End If

                        Set f to f plus 1
                    End While
                End If

                Set p to p plus 1
            End While
        End If

        Set c to c plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Solidity convention: contract/interface/library names use CapWords
(PascalCase) - the first character must be an uppercase ASCII letter.
A leading lowercase or non-letter is a style violation that this pass
records as a warning (not an error - it does not affect correctness).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates the contracts registry @0 (and interfaces @8, libraries @16).
For each name, reads the first character; if it is not in the range
'A'..'Z' (65..90), records a "Contract name should be CapWords: <name>"
warning via add_solidity_validation_warning.
@End Implementation
Process called "check_contract_naming_conventions" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Warn on contract/interface/library names that are not CapWords

    proc check_registry_naming_conventions with analyzer, 0, "Contract"
    proc check_registry_naming_conventions with analyzer, 8, "Interface"
    proc check_registry_naming_conventions with analyzer, 16, "Library"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Shared helper for check_contract_naming_conventions: applies the CapWords
first-character check to every key of one registry, with a label
identifying the declaration kind in the warning message.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the registry Dict at the given analyzer offset, lists its keys, and
for each name reads the first character via string_char_at. If the
character is below 'A' (65) or above 'Z' (90), appends a
"<label> name should be CapWords: <name>" warning.
@End Implementation
Process called "check_registry_naming_conventions" takes analyzer as Integer, offset as Integer, label as Integer:
    Note: CapWords first-character check over one declaration registry

    Let registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, offset
    Let names be proc keys from Dict with registry
    Let count be proc size from List with names
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than count:
        Let name be proc get from List with names, i
        Let name_length be proc string_length from StringCore with name

        If name_length is greater than 0:
            Let first_char be proc string_char_at from StringCore with name, 0
            Let below_upper be 0
            Let above_upper be 0
            If first_char is less than 65:
                Set below_upper to 1
            End If
            If first_char is greater than 90:
                Set above_upper to 1
            End If

            If below_upper is equal to 1:
                Let warning be proc string_concat from StringPrim with label, " name should be CapWords: "
                Set warning to proc string_concat from StringPrim with warning, name
                proc add_solidity_validation_warning with analyzer, warning
            Otherwise:
                If above_upper is equal to 1:
                    Let warning2 be proc string_concat from StringPrim with label, " name should be CapWords: "
                    Set warning2 to proc string_concat from StringPrim with warning2, name
                    proc add_solidity_validation_warning with analyzer, warning2
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: SECURITY SUB-PASSES (per-function)
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Per-function arithmetic-safety analysis. Solidity 0.8+ checks arithmetic
by default, but code inside `unchecked { ... }` blocks opts out, so any
arithmetic operation (+, -, *) found beneath an unchecked block is a real
overflow/underflow exposure. This pass walks the function body counting
arithmetic operations that occur inside unchecked regions and records a
risk when any are found.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the function body; if absent returns. Walks the body with
count_unchecked_arithmetic which descends recursively, tracking whether
the current subtree is under an unchecked block (the parser marks such
blocks; detected via the block's value/metadata). Each arithmetic
SOL_BINARY_EXPR (operator +, -, *, **) under an unchecked region
increments the counter. If the count is positive, appends
"Unchecked arithmetic in function: <name>" to overflow_risks @144.
@End Implementation
Process called "analyze_function_arithmetic_safety" takes analyzer as Integer, function_name as Integer, function_def as Integer:
    Note: Flag arithmetic in unchecked blocks as overflow/underflow risk

    Let function_body be proc get_solidity_function_body with function_def
    If function_body is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let unchecked_arith be proc count_unchecked_arithmetic with function_body, 0
    If unchecked_arith is greater than 0:
        Let overflow_risks be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 144
        Let risk_msg be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Unchecked arithmetic in function: ", function_name
        proc add from List with overflow_risks, risk_msg
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Recursive worker for arithmetic safety. The 'in_unchecked' flag is set
once the walk descends below an unchecked or assembly block and
propagates to all descendants. Arithmetic binary operators encountered
while the flag is set are counted. Solidity's `unchecked { ... }` block is
parsed as SOL_UNCHECKED_BLOCK (the explicit opt-out of 0.8+ default
checks); raw assembly (SOL_ASSEMBLY_BLOCK) likewise bypasses language-level
overflow protection. Treating both as unchecked regions and otherwise
propagating the inherited flag yields a correct, conservative count of
arithmetic that runs without overflow protection.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns 0 for null. Computes the effective unchecked flag for this node:
inherited flag OR (node type == SOL_UNCHECKED_BLOCK) OR
(node type == SOL_ASSEMBLY_BLOCK). If the node is a SOL_BINARY_EXPR with
an arithmetic operator (+, -, *, **) and the effective flag is set,
contributes 1. Recurses into the left/right metadata operands and into
children, summing their counts, and returns the total.
@End Implementation
Process called "count_unchecked_arithmetic" takes node as Integer, in_unchecked as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Count arithmetic operations executing without overflow protection

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with node

    Let effective_unchecked be in_unchecked
    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_UNCHECKED_BLOCK:
        Set effective_unchecked to 1
    End If
    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_ASSEMBLY_BLOCK:
        Set effective_unchecked to 1
    End If

    Let total be 0

    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_BINARY_EXPR:
        If effective_unchecked is equal to 1:
            Let op be proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with node
            Let is_arith be proc is_arithmetic_operator with op
            If is_arith is equal to 1:
                Set total to total plus 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with node

    Let left_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "left"
    If left_node is not equal to 0:
        Let lc be proc count_unchecked_arithmetic with left_node, effective_unchecked
        Set total to total plus lc
    End If

    Let right_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "right"
    If right_node is not equal to 0:
        Let rc be proc count_unchecked_arithmetic with right_node, effective_unchecked
        Set total to total plus rc
    End If

    Let operand_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "operand"
    If operand_node is not equal to 0:
        Let oc be proc count_unchecked_arithmetic with operand_node, effective_unchecked
        Set total to total plus oc
    End If

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with node
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return total
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let cc be proc count_unchecked_arithmetic with child, effective_unchecked
        Set total to total plus cc
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return total
End Process

@Reasoning:
Classifies an operator string as overflow-capable arithmetic: +, -, *,
**. Division and modulo cannot overflow in the two's-complement sense
(division by zero is a separate revert), so they are excluded.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Compares the operator against "+", "-", "*", "**" with string_equals,
returning 1 on the first match, else 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "is_arithmetic_operator" takes op as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Test whether an operator can overflow/underflow

    If op is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let is_add be proc string_equals from StringCore with op, "+"
    If is_add is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let is_sub be proc string_equals from StringCore with op, "-"
    If is_sub is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let is_mul be proc string_equals from StringCore with op, "*"
    If is_mul is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let is_pow be proc string_equals from StringCore with op, "**"
    If is_pow is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Per-function access-control analysis. A state-mutating, externally
reachable function (public/external, non-view/pure) that carries no
access-control modifier and writes state is a privilege risk - anyone can
invoke it. This pass flags such functions so a reviewer can confirm the
omission is intentional (e.g. a deliberately open mint is rare).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Determines the function visibility and mutability via the accessors. If
visibility is public or external AND mutability is neither view nor pure
AND the function body contains a state change AND the function carries no
recognised access-control modifier (a modifier other than the
visibility/mutability/virtual/override keywords - i.e. a user-defined
guard like onlyOwner) THEN records
"Function <name> changes state without an access-control modifier" into
access_control_issues @152.
@End Implementation
Process called "analyze_function_access_control" takes analyzer as Integer, function_name as Integer, function_def as Integer:
    Note: Flag externally-reachable state-mutating functions lacking a guard

    Let visibility be proc get_solidity_function_visibility with function_def
    Let is_public be proc string_equals from StringCore with visibility, "public"
    Let is_external be proc string_equals from StringCore with visibility, "external"

    Let externally_reachable be 0
    If is_public is equal to 1:
        Set externally_reachable to 1
    End If
    If is_external is equal to 1:
        Set externally_reachable to 1
    End If

    If externally_reachable is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let mutability be proc get_solidity_function_state_mutability with function_def
    Let is_view be proc string_equals from StringCore with mutability, "view"
    Let is_pure be proc string_equals from StringCore with mutability, "pure"
    If is_view is equal to 1:
        Return
    End If
    If is_pure is equal to 1:
        Return
    End If

    Let function_body be proc get_solidity_function_body with function_def
    If function_body is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let mutates be proc contains_state_changes with function_body
    If mutates is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let has_guard be proc function_has_access_guard with function_def
    If has_guard is equal to 0:
        Let access_control_issues be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 152
        Let msg be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Function ", function_name
        Set msg to proc string_concat from StringPrim with msg, " changes state without an access-control modifier"
        proc add from List with access_control_issues, msg
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Decides whether a function carries a user-defined access-control guard.
The parser collects ALL modifier keywords (visibility, mutability,
virtual, override, AND user-defined modifier names like onlyOwner) into
the same "modifiers" list. A user-defined guard is therefore any modifier
entry that is NOT one of the reserved language keywords. The presence of
such an entry indicates an access guard is applied.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the function "modifiers" List. For each entry, if it is not one of
the reserved keywords (public/private/internal/external/pure/view/
payable/virtual/override) it is a user-defined modifier and the function
is considered guarded (returns 1). Returns 0 when every entry is a
reserved keyword.
@End Implementation
Process called "function_has_access_guard" takes function_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Detect a user-defined (non-reserved) modifier on a function

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with function_def
    Let modifiers be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "modifiers"
    If modifiers is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with modifiers
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let modifier be proc get from List with modifiers, i
        Let reserved be proc is_reserved_modifier_keyword with modifier
        If reserved is equal to 0:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Classifies a modifier-list entry as a reserved Solidity keyword (the
visibility, mutability, and inheritance flags the parser also stores in
the modifiers list) versus a user-defined modifier name. Used to isolate
user-defined access guards.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Compares the entry against the nine reserved keywords (public, private,
internal, external, pure, view, payable, virtual, override) with
string_equals, returning 1 on any match, else 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "is_reserved_modifier_keyword" takes keyword as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Test whether a modifier entry is a reserved language keyword

    If keyword is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let k1 be proc string_equals from StringCore with keyword, "public"
    If k1 is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let k2 be proc string_equals from StringCore with keyword, "private"
    If k2 is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let k3 be proc string_equals from StringCore with keyword, "internal"
    If k3 is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let k4 be proc string_equals from StringCore with keyword, "external"
    If k4 is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let k5 be proc string_equals from StringCore with keyword, "pure"
    If k5 is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let k6 be proc string_equals from StringCore with keyword, "view"
    If k6 is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let k7 be proc string_equals from StringCore with keyword, "payable"
    If k7 is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let k8 be proc string_equals from StringCore with keyword, "virtual"
    If k8 is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let k9 be proc string_equals from StringCore with keyword, "override"
    If k9 is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Flags unchecked low-level external calls. The low-level call/send return
a boolean success flag that, if ignored, lets a failed transfer pass
silently. This pass detects functions that contain a low-level external
call whose boolean result is not consumed (the call is a bare expression
statement rather than the condition of a require/if), and records a
security issue.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates functions_registry @48. For each function body, walks for a
SOL_CALL_EXPR or SOL_MEMBER_EXPR external call (call/send/delegatecall)
that appears as a direct statement child of a block (its result discarded)
rather than nested inside a condition. Detected occurrences append
"Unchecked low-level call in function: <name>" to security_issues @120.
@End Implementation
Process called "check_unchecked_external_calls" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Detect low-level external calls whose success flag is ignored

    Let functions_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 48
    Let security_issues be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 120
    Let function_names be proc keys from Dict with functions_registry
    Let func_count be proc size from List with function_names
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than func_count:
        Let function_name be proc get from List with function_names, i
        Let function_def be proc get from Dict with functions_registry, function_name
        Let function_body be proc get_solidity_function_body with function_def

        If function_body is not equal to 0:
            Let unchecked_call be proc has_unchecked_low_level_call with function_body
            If unchecked_call is equal to 1:
                Let msg be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Unchecked low-level call in function: ", function_name
                proc add from List with security_issues, msg
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Detects a low-level external call appearing as a discarded statement. A
block's direct children are statements; if one of them is itself an
external-call expression (or an expression statement wrapping one) whose
result is not bound, the success flag is ignored. This walks block
children one level looking for such bare calls, descending through nested
blocks/control statements so calls deep in the body are still caught.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Recurses over the node. When the node is a SOL_BLOCK_STMT, iterates its
children: any child that is directly an external call node (node_is_external_call)
is a discarded low-level call -> returns 1. Otherwise recurses into each
child (to reach nested blocks). For non-block nodes, recurses into block
children only (it does not descend into the operand of a require/if
condition, where the result IS consumed). Returns 0 when none found.
@End Implementation
Process called "has_unchecked_low_level_call" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Find a bare (result-discarded) low-level external call

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with node

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with node
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i

        If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_BLOCK_STMT:
            Let bare_call be proc node_is_external_call with child
            If bare_call is equal to 1:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If

        Let nested be proc has_unchecked_low_level_call with child
        If nested is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validates that externally-reachable functions taking reference-type or
address parameters perform input validation (a require/revert guard).
Missing validation on address parameters is a common vector for
zero-address and unauthorized-input bugs. This pass flags public/external
functions whose body contains no require/revert guard while accepting
parameters.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates functions_registry @48. For each public/external function with
at least one parameter, walks the body for any SOL_CALL_EXPR named
"require" / "assert" or a SOL_REVERT_STMT. If none is present, appends
"Function <name> lacks input validation" to validation_warnings @168 (a
warning, not a hard error, since validation may be enforced elsewhere).
@End Implementation
Process called "validate_input_validation" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Warn on externally-reachable functions with no input validation

    Let functions_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 48
    Let function_names be proc keys from Dict with functions_registry
    Let func_count be proc size from List with function_names
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than func_count:
        Let function_name be proc get from List with function_names, i
        Let function_def be proc get from Dict with functions_registry, function_name

        Let visibility be proc get_solidity_function_visibility with function_def
        Let is_public be proc string_equals from StringCore with visibility, "public"
        Let is_external be proc string_equals from StringCore with visibility, "external"

        Let externally_reachable be 0
        If is_public is equal to 1:
            Set externally_reachable to 1
        End If
        If is_external is equal to 1:
            Set externally_reachable to 1
        End If

        If externally_reachable is equal to 1:
            Let param_count be proc count_function_parameters with function_def
            If param_count is greater than 0:
                Let function_body be proc get_solidity_function_body with function_def
                If function_body is not equal to 0:
                    Let has_validation be proc body_has_validation_guard with function_body
                    If has_validation is equal to 0:
                        Let warning be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Function ", function_name
                        Set warning to proc string_concat from StringPrim with warning, " lacks input validation"
                        proc add_solidity_validation_warning with analyzer, warning
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Counts a function's declared parameters by tallying its SOL_PARAMETER
children. Returns the count so the input-validation pass can skip
zero-arg functions (which have no inputs to validate).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates function children, incrementing for each whose type is
SOL_PARAMETER. Returns the total.
@End Implementation
Process called "count_function_parameters" takes function_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Count SOL_PARAMETER children of a function

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with function_def
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let count be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with child
        If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_PARAMETER:
            Set count to count plus 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return count
End Process

@Reasoning:
Detects whether a function body contains a validation guard: a call to
require/assert or a revert statement. Used by validate_input_validation
to decide whether inputs are checked. Recurses the whole body because a
guard may be nested inside the first block.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Recursively walks the body. Returns 1 when the node is a SOL_REVERT_STMT,
or a SOL_CALL_EXPR whose callee name (node value, or the "function"
metadata member name) equals "require" or "assert". Otherwise recurses
into metadata sub-expressions and children. Returns 0 when none found.
@End Implementation
Process called "body_has_validation_guard" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Recursively detect a require/assert/revert guard

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with node

    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_REVERT_STMT:
        Return 1
    End If

    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_CALL_EXPR:
        Let callee_name be proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with node
        Let is_require be proc string_equals from StringCore with callee_name, "require"
        If is_require is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Let is_assert be proc string_equals from StringCore with callee_name, "assert"
        If is_assert is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with node
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let found be proc body_has_validation_guard with child
        If found is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: GAS SUB-PASSES (per-element)
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Per-state-variable gas advisory. Public state variables auto-generate a
getter (extra bytecode), and non-constant/non-immutable configuration
that is written once wastes a storage slot's worth of gas on every read
versus immutable. This pass advises on storage cost where the declaration
form suggests an avoidable expense.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the variable's visibility and mutability via the accessors. If the
variable is public, appends "State variable <name> is public (auto-getter
adds bytecode); consider explicit getter if not needed" to gas_warnings
@128. Independent of that, if the variable is neither constant nor
immutable, appends "State variable <name> is mutable; if write-once mark
it immutable/constant to save gas". Both are advisories.
@End Implementation
Process called "analyze_storage_variable_gas" takes analyzer as Integer, var_name as Integer, state_var as Integer:
    Note: Advise on storage-variable gas cost from its declaration form

    Let gas_warnings be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 128

    Let visibility be proc get_solidity_state_variable_visibility with state_var
    Let is_public be proc string_equals from StringCore with visibility, "public"
    If is_public is equal to 1:
        Let warning be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "State variable ", var_name
        Set warning to proc string_concat from StringPrim with warning, " is public (auto-getter adds bytecode); consider explicit getter if not needed"
        proc add from List with gas_warnings, warning
    End If

    Let mutability be proc get_solidity_state_variable_mutability with state_var
    Let is_constant be proc string_equals from StringCore with mutability, "constant"
    Let is_immutable be proc string_equals from StringCore with mutability, "immutable"

    If is_constant is equal to 0:
        If is_immutable is equal to 0:
            Let warning2 be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "State variable ", var_name
            Set warning2 to proc string_concat from StringPrim with warning2, " is mutable; if write-once mark it immutable/constant to save gas"
            proc add from List with gas_warnings, warning2
        End If
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Per-function loop gas advisory. Loops are the primary source of
out-of-gas reverts: an unbounded loop (no constant bound) or a loop body
that performs storage writes scales gas with iteration count and can
exceed the block gas limit. This pass counts loop constructs in the
function body and advises when any are present, and specifically flags
storage writes inside loops.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the function body; if absent returns. Walks the body counting
SOL_FOR_STMT and SOL_WHILE_STMT nodes (loop_count) and separately whether
any such loop contains a state change (storage write) in its body. If
loop_count > 0, appends "Function <name> contains loops; verify bounded
iteration to avoid out-of-gas" to gas_warnings @128. If a loop with an
inner state change is found, additionally appends
"Function <name> writes storage inside a loop; gas scales with iterations".
@End Implementation
Process called "check_function_loop_gas_limits" takes analyzer as Integer, function_name as Integer, function_def as Integer:
    Note: Advise on loop-driven gas costs in a function body

    Let function_body be proc get_solidity_function_body with function_def
    If function_body is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let gas_warnings be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 128

    Let loop_count be proc count_loops with function_body
    If loop_count is greater than 0:
        Let warning be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Function ", function_name
        Set warning to proc string_concat from StringPrim with warning, " contains loops; verify bounded iteration to avoid out-of-gas"
        proc add from List with gas_warnings, warning

        Let storage_in_loop be proc loop_contains_state_change with function_body
        If storage_in_loop is equal to 1:
            Let warning2 be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Function ", function_name
            Set warning2 to proc string_concat from StringPrim with warning2, " writes storage inside a loop; gas scales with iterations"
            proc add from List with gas_warnings, warning2
        End If
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Counts loop constructs (for, while) anywhere in a subtree. Used by the
loop-gas advisory to decide whether any loops exist.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Recursive count. Adds 1 when the node type is SOL_FOR_STMT or
SOL_WHILE_STMT, then sums recursive counts over metadata sub-expressions
(body/condition) and children.
@End Implementation
Process called "count_loops" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Recursively count for/while loop constructs

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with node
    Let total be 0

    Let is_for be 0
    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_FOR_STMT:
        Set is_for to 1
    End If
    Let is_while be 0
    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_WHILE_STMT:
        Set is_while to 1
    End If
    If is_for is equal to 1:
        Set total to total plus 1
    End If
    If is_while is equal to 1:
        Set total to total plus 1
    End If

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with node

    Let body_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "body"
    If body_node is not equal to 0:
        Let bc be proc count_loops with body_node
        Set total to total plus bc
    End If

    Let condition_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "condition"
    If condition_node is not equal to 0:
        Let cc be proc count_loops with condition_node
        Set total to total plus cc
    End If

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with node
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return total
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let rc be proc count_loops with child
        Set total to total plus rc
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return total
End Process

@Reasoning:
Determines whether any loop body in the subtree performs a state change.
A storage write inside a loop is the expensive pattern the gas advisory
calls out specifically. Walks to each loop node and tests its body
subtree with contains_state_changes.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Recurses the tree. On a SOL_FOR_STMT or SOL_WHILE_STMT node, reads the
loop "body" metadata (or scans children for a SOL_BLOCK_STMT) and runs
contains_state_changes on it; returns 1 on a hit. Otherwise recurses into
children. Returns 0 when no loop contains a state change.
@End Implementation
Process called "loop_contains_state_change" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Detect a storage write inside any loop body

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with node

    Let is_loop be 0
    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_FOR_STMT:
        Set is_loop to 1
    End If
    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_WHILE_STMT:
        Set is_loop to 1
    End If

    If is_loop is equal to 1:
        Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with node
        Let body_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "body"
        If body_node is not equal to 0:
            Let mutates be proc contains_state_changes with body_node
            If mutates is equal to 1:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If

        Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with node
        If children is not equal to 0:
            Let child_count be proc size from List with children
            Let k be 0
            While k is less than child_count:
                Let child be proc get from List with children, k
                Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with child
                If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_BLOCK_STMT:
                    Let mutates2 be proc contains_state_changes with child
                    If mutates2 is equal to 1:
                        Return 1
                    End If
                End If
                Set k to k plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If

    Let all_children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with node
    If all_children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let total_children be proc size from List with all_children
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than total_children:
        Let sub be proc get from List with all_children, i
        Let found be proc loop_contains_state_change with sub
        If found is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
General gas-optimization advisor over all functions. Two language-level
optimizations are detectable structurally: external functions reading
calldata reference parameters should declare them `calldata` not `memory`
(avoids a copy), and small uint types in storage that could be packed.
This pass advises where the declaration form leaves gas on the table.
Functions whose body is empty are skipped.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates functions_registry @48. For each public/external function, scans
its SOL_PARAMETER children: a reference-type parameter (its "type" node is
a SOL_ARRAY_TYPE or the type name is a non-elementary identifier) with no
calldata location triggers
"Function <name> parameter could use calldata to save gas" in
gas_warnings @128. Each advisory is added once per offending parameter.
@End Implementation
Process called "identify_gas_optimizations" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Advise on calldata/parameter gas optimizations across functions

    Let functions_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 48
    Let gas_warnings be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 128
    Let function_names be proc keys from Dict with functions_registry
    Let func_count be proc size from List with function_names
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than func_count:
        Let function_name be proc get from List with function_names, i
        Let function_def be proc get from Dict with functions_registry, function_name

        Let visibility be proc get_solidity_function_visibility with function_def
        Let is_external be proc string_equals from StringCore with visibility, "external"

        If is_external is equal to 1:
            Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with function_def
            If children is not equal to 0:
                Let child_count be proc size from List with children
                Let c be 0
                While c is less than child_count:
                    Let child be proc get from List with children, c
                    Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with child
                    If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_PARAMETER:
                        Let needs_calldata be proc parameter_is_reference_without_calldata with child
                        If needs_calldata is equal to 1:
                            Let warning be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Function ", function_name
                            Set warning to proc string_concat from StringPrim with warning, " parameter could use calldata to save gas"
                            proc add from List with gas_warnings, warning
                        End If
                    End If
                    Set c to c plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Decides whether a parameter is a reference type (array or mapping) that
lacks a calldata data location. Reference parameters of external
functions are cheaper as calldata than memory. The parser stores the
parameter type under "type" and its data location under "storage".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the parameter's "type" node and "storage" location from metadata.
If the type node's type is SOL_ARRAY_TYPE or SOL_MAPPING_TYPE (reference
types) AND the storage location is not "calldata", returns 1. Otherwise
returns 0 (elementary value types do not benefit).
@End Implementation
Process called "parameter_is_reference_without_calldata" takes param as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Test for a reference-type parameter not declared calldata

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with param
    Let type_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "type"
    If type_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let type_kind be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with type_node
    Let is_reference be 0
    If type_kind is equal to Parser.SOL_ARRAY_TYPE:
        Set is_reference to 1
    End If
    If type_kind is equal to Parser.SOL_MAPPING_TYPE:
        Set is_reference to 1
    End If

    If is_reference is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let storage_location be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "storage"
    If storage_location is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let is_calldata be proc string_equals from StringCore with storage_location, "calldata"
    If is_calldata is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validates that explicit gas hints, where present, are sensible. Solidity
permits `{gas: N}` and `{value: N}` call options; a gas hint of zero
forces the sub-call to fail. This pass scans every function body for
call-option metadata carrying a literal-zero gas value and flags it. With
no explicit gas hints present, the pass is a no-op (the default gas
forwarding is correct).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates functions_registry @48. For each function body, walks for
SOL_CALL_EXPR nodes carrying a "gas" metadata sub-expression; when that
sub-expression is a numeric literal equal to "0", appends
"Function <name> forwards zero gas in a call (sub-call will fail)" to
gas_warnings @128.
@End Implementation
Process called "validate_gas_estimates" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Flag explicit zero-gas call hints across functions

    Let functions_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 48
    Let gas_warnings be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 128
    Let function_names be proc keys from Dict with functions_registry
    Let func_count be proc size from List with function_names
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than func_count:
        Let function_name be proc get from List with function_names, i
        Let function_def be proc get from Dict with functions_registry, function_name
        Let function_body be proc get_solidity_function_body with function_def

        If function_body is not equal to 0:
            Let has_zero_gas be proc body_has_zero_gas_hint with function_body
            If has_zero_gas is equal to 1:
                Let warning be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Function ", function_name
                Set warning to proc string_concat from StringPrim with warning, " forwards zero gas in a call (sub-call will fail)"
                proc add from List with gas_warnings, warning
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Detects a call carrying an explicit gas option of literal zero anywhere
in a subtree. A forwarded gas of 0 guarantees the sub-call reverts, which
is almost always a bug. Walks the tree testing each SOL_CALL_EXPR's "gas"
metadata.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Recurses the tree. On a SOL_CALL_EXPR node, reads "gas" metadata; if that
sub-node is a SOL_NUMBER_LITERAL whose value equals "0", returns 1.
Otherwise recurses into the "function"/"object" metadata and children.
Returns 0 when no zero-gas hint is found.
@End Implementation
Process called "body_has_zero_gas_hint" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Recursively detect a literal-zero gas call option

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with node
    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with node

    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_CALL_EXPR:
        Let gas_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "gas"
        If gas_node is not equal to 0:
            Let gas_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with gas_node
            If gas_type is equal to Parser.SOL_NUMBER_LITERAL:
                Let gas_value be proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with gas_node
                Let is_zero be proc string_equals from StringCore with gas_value, "0"
                If is_zero is equal to 1:
                    Return 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let function_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "function"
    If function_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r be proc body_has_zero_gas_hint with function_node
        If r is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let object_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "object"
    If object_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r2 be proc body_has_zero_gas_hint with object_node
        If r2 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with node
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let rc be proc body_has_zero_gas_hint with child
        If rc is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: DECLARATION VALIDATION SUB-PASSES
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Per-modifier validation. A Solidity modifier body must contain the
placeholder statement `_;` exactly once on every execution path for the
guarded function to ever run; a modifier whose body has no placeholder
silently blocks the function. This pass checks for the presence of the
placeholder and warns when it is absent.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the modifier name and body. Walks the body looking for the
placeholder identifier ("_"). If none is found, appends
"Modifier <Contract>.<name> has no placeholder (_;) and blocks its
function" to validation_warnings @168.
@End Implementation
Process called "validate_modifier_declaration" takes analyzer as Integer, contract_name as Integer, modifier_def as Integer:
    Note: Warn on a modifier body lacking the _; placeholder

    Let modifier_name be proc get_solidity_modifier_name with modifier_def

    Let body be 0
    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with modifier_def
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let child_count be proc size from List with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than child_count:
            Let child be proc get from List with children, i
            Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with child
            If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_BLOCK_STMT:
                Set body to child
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    If body is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let has_placeholder be proc body_has_placeholder with body
    If has_placeholder is equal to 0:
        Let warning be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Modifier ", contract_name
        Set warning to proc string_concat from StringPrim with warning, "."
        Set warning to proc string_concat from StringPrim with warning, modifier_name
        Set warning to proc string_concat from StringPrim with warning, " has no placeholder (_;) and blocks its function"
        proc add_solidity_validation_warning with analyzer, warning
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Detects the modifier placeholder statement `_;` in a body subtree. The
parser emits the placeholder as an identifier whose value is "_" (the
lexer tokenises "_" as an ordinary identifier and the statement parser
wraps it). Recursive presence test descending through statement children.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Recurses. Returns 1 when the node is a SOL_IDENTIFIER whose value equals
"_". Otherwise recurses into children. Returns 0 when none found.
@End Implementation
Process called "body_has_placeholder" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Recursively detect the _; modifier placeholder

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with node

    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_IDENTIFIER:
        Let value be proc solidity_ast_value from Parser with node
        Let is_underscore be proc string_equals from StringCore with value, "_"
        If is_underscore is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with node
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let found be proc body_has_placeholder with child
        If found is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Special-function naming/structure rules. Constructors, receive, and
fallback functions have specific requirements: constructors cannot have a
visibility of private and must not be named like a regular function in
0.8+; receive() must be external payable; fallback() must be external.
This pass enforces the rules that are checkable from the declaration.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads func_name. If the name equals "receive", verifies the function is
external and payable (via the accessors) and records an error if not. If
the name equals "fallback", verifies it is external and records an error
if not. For ordinary names no special rule applies. Constructor nodes are
a distinct AST type (SOL_CONSTRUCTOR) and are not routed here, so this
pass focuses on the receive/fallback special functions reachable as
SOL_FUNCTION with reserved names.
@End Implementation
Process called "validate_special_function_rules" takes analyzer as Integer, func_name as Integer, function_def as Integer:
    Note: Enforce receive/fallback declaration rules

    Let is_receive be proc string_equals from StringCore with func_name, "receive"
    If is_receive is equal to 1:
        Let visibility be proc get_solidity_function_visibility with function_def
        Let mutability be proc get_solidity_function_state_mutability with function_def
        Let is_external be proc string_equals from StringCore with visibility, "external"
        Let is_payable be proc string_equals from StringCore with mutability, "payable"

        If is_external is equal to 0:
            proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, "receive() must be declared external"
        End If
        If is_payable is equal to 0:
            proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, "receive() must be declared payable"
        End If
        Return
    End If

    Let is_fallback be proc string_equals from StringCore with func_name, "fallback"
    If is_fallback is equal to 1:
        Let fb_visibility be proc get_solidity_function_visibility with function_def
        Let fb_is_external be proc string_equals from StringCore with fb_visibility, "external"
        If fb_is_external is equal to 0:
            proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, "fallback() must be declared external"
        End If
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Naming-convention checker shared by state variables and other named
elements. Solidity style: variables and functions are mixedCase (first
character lowercase), constants are UPPER_SNAKE. This pass applies the
mixedCase first-character rule and warns on a leading uppercase letter
for non-constant elements.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the first character of the name. If it is an uppercase ASCII letter
(65..90), appends "<element_type> name should be mixedCase: <name>" to
validation_warnings @168. Empty names are skipped.
@End Implementation
Process called "check_solidity_naming_conventions" takes analyzer as Integer, name as Integer, element_type as Integer:
    Note: Warn on a non-mixedCase identifier name

    Let name_length be proc string_length from StringCore with name
    If name_length is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let first_char be proc string_char_at from StringCore with name, 0

    Let starts_upper be 0
    If first_char is greater than or equal to 65:
        If first_char is less than or equal to 90:
            Set starts_upper to 1
        End If
    End If

    If starts_upper is equal to 1:
        Let warning be proc string_concat from StringPrim with element_type, " name should be mixedCase: "
        Set warning to proc string_concat from StringPrim with warning, name
        proc add_solidity_validation_warning with analyzer, warning
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: TYPE VALIDATION SUB-PASSES
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Per-signature validation worker. The function-signature pass iterates
qualified names; this worker validates an individual synthesized
signature string is well-formed: it must contain a "(" and a closing ")"
delimiting the parameter list. A signature missing either delimiter
indicates a synthesis or parse defect and is recorded as an error.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the signature string length. Scans for the first "(" and the last
")" by character. If either is absent (no open paren, or no close paren
after the open), appends "Malformed function signature: <qualified>" to
validation_errors @160.
@End Implementation
Process called "validate_individual_function_signature" takes analyzer as Integer, func_name as Integer, function_sig as Integer:
    Note: Validate a synthesized signature has balanced parentheses

    If function_sig is equal to 0:
        Let error be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Malformed function signature: ", func_name
        proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, error
        Return
    End If

    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with function_sig
    Let open_index be 0 minus 1
    Let close_index be 0 minus 1
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than length:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with function_sig, i
        If ch is equal to 40:
            If open_index is less than 0:
                Set open_index to i
            End If
        End If
        If ch is equal to 41:
            Set close_index to i
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Let malformed be 0
    If open_index is less than 0:
        Set malformed to 1
    End If
    If close_index is less than open_index:
        Set malformed to 1
    End If

    If malformed is equal to 1:
        Let error2 be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Malformed function signature: ", func_name
        proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, error2
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Cross-checks assignment type compatibility for state variable
initializers. A state variable declared with an initializer must have a
type-compatible right-hand side. Full type inference is the job of a
dedicated type-inference engine; at this layer the achievable, correct
check is that an initializer expression is present and well-formed when
the declaration includes the `=` form. This pass verifies every
initialized state variable carries a non-null initializer node.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates state_variables @40. For each, reads its metadata "initializer";
if the declaration syntactically had an initializer slot that resolved to
0 (a parse defect), records "Malformed initializer for state variable:
<qualified>" to validation_errors @160. Variables with no initializer at
all are skipped (uninitialized state is legal and defaults to zero).
@End Implementation
Process called "check_type_compatibility" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Validate state-variable initializers are well-formed nodes

    Let state_variables be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 40
    Let var_names be proc keys from Dict with state_variables
    Let var_count be proc size from List with var_names
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than var_count:
        Let var_name be proc get from List with var_names, i
        Let state_var be proc get from Dict with state_variables, var_name

        Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with state_var
        Let has_init_key be proc metadata_has_key with metadata, "initializer"
        If has_init_key is equal to 1:
            Let initializer be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "initializer"
            If initializer is equal to 0:
                Let error be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Malformed initializer for state variable: ", var_name
                proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, error
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Tests whether a metadata key is present at all (distinct from its value
being 0). Needed because check_type_compatibility must distinguish "no
initializer declared" (key absent, legal) from "initializer slot present
but null" (key present with 0 value, a defect).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Scans the flat metadata list in steps of two comparing each key with
string_equals; returns 1 if the key appears, else 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "metadata_has_key" takes metadata as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Test presence of a metadata key regardless of its value

    If metadata is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with metadata
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let entry_key be proc get from List with metadata, i
        Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with entry_key, key
        If matches is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 2
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validates explicit type conversions in function bodies. Solidity allows
unsafe narrowing casts (e.g. uint256 -> uint8) that silently truncate;
this pass flags explicit casts to a smaller elementary type as a warning
so the developer confirms the truncation is intended.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates functions_registry @48. For each function body, walks for
SOL_TYPE_CAST nodes; each cast carries its target type and operand. When
a cast is present, appends "Explicit type conversion in function <name>;
verify no unintended truncation" to validation_warnings @168. Bodies with
no casts produce no output.
@End Implementation
Process called "validate_type_conversions" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Warn on explicit type conversions that may truncate

    Let functions_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 48
    Let function_names be proc keys from Dict with functions_registry
    Let func_count be proc size from List with function_names
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than func_count:
        Let function_name be proc get from List with function_names, i
        Let function_def be proc get from Dict with functions_registry, function_name
        Let function_body be proc get_solidity_function_body with function_def

        If function_body is not equal to 0:
            Let has_cast be proc body_has_type_cast with function_body
            If has_cast is equal to 1:
                Let warning be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Explicit type conversion in function ", function_name
                Set warning to proc string_concat from StringPrim with warning, "; verify no unintended truncation"
                proc add_solidity_validation_warning with analyzer, warning
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Detects any explicit type cast in a subtree. Recursive presence test over
SOL_TYPE_CAST nodes, used by validate_type_conversions.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Recurses. Returns 1 when the node type is SOL_TYPE_CAST. Otherwise
recurses into the "operand"/"object" metadata sub-expressions and
children. Returns 0 when no cast is present.
@End Implementation
Process called "body_has_type_cast" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Recursively detect an explicit SOL_TYPE_CAST

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with node
    If node_type is equal to Parser.SOL_TYPE_CAST:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with node

    Let operand_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "operand"
    If operand_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r be proc body_has_type_cast with operand_node
        If r is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let object_node be proc get_ast_meta_value with metadata, "object"
    If object_node is not equal to 0:
        Let r2 be proc body_has_type_cast with object_node
        If r2 is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with node
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let child_count be proc size from List with children
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc get from List with children, i
        Let rc be proc body_has_type_cast with child
        If rc is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validates ABI-encoding compatibility for external/public functions. The
externally-callable ABI cannot encode certain types as parameters or
return values in older encodings; the universally checkable rule is that
external function parameters and returns must be ABI-representable, which
for the structural checker means every external function's signature was
synthesised without an empty type segment (a missing parameter type makes
the selector unencodable). This pass re-derives each external function's
signature and flags any with an empty parameter type segment.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Iterates functions_registry @48. For each public/external function,
iterates its SOL_PARAMETER children; if any parameter's "type" metadata
is 0 (no type), appends "Function <name> has an ABI-incompatible
parameter (missing type)" to validation_errors @160.
@End Implementation
Process called "check_abi_encoding_compatibility" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Validate external function parameters are ABI-encodable

    Let functions_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 48
    Let function_names be proc keys from Dict with functions_registry
    Let func_count be proc size from List with function_names
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than func_count:
        Let function_name be proc get from List with function_names, i
        Let function_def be proc get from Dict with functions_registry, function_name

        Let visibility be proc get_solidity_function_visibility with function_def
        Let is_public be proc string_equals from StringCore with visibility, "public"
        Let is_external be proc string_equals from StringCore with visibility, "external"

        Let externally_reachable be 0
        If is_public is equal to 1:
            Set externally_reachable to 1
        End If
        If is_external is equal to 1:
            Set externally_reachable to 1
        End If

        If externally_reachable is equal to 1:
            Let children be proc solidity_ast_children from Parser with function_def
            If children is not equal to 0:
                Let child_count be proc size from List with children
                Let c be 0
                While c is less than child_count:
                    Let child be proc get from List with children, c
                    Let child_type be proc solidity_ast_type from Parser with child
                    If child_type is equal to Parser.SOL_PARAMETER:
                        Let param_metadata be proc solidity_ast_metadata from Parser with child
                        Let param_type be proc get_ast_meta_value with param_metadata, "type"
                        If param_type is equal to 0:
                            Let error be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "Function ", function_name
                            Set error to proc string_concat from StringPrim with error, " has an ABI-incompatible parameter (missing type)"
                            proc add_solidity_validation_error with analyzer, error
                        End If
                    End If
                    Set c to c plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process